"score":1},{"id":"recYsXWjhw6FUqHLY","type":"place","group":"mentioned","label":"Gibeon","slug":"gibeon_470","score":1}],"links":[{"source":"rec1FAvujLYvBJfHg","target":"rec2ZFQHqI4eUjhqX","label":"part of"},{"source":"rec1FAvujLYvBJfHg","target":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1FAvujLYvBJfHg","target":"rec1ZMFtfbEvoGC73","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1FAvujLYvBJfHg","target":"recbSbqQdmphYflev","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1FAvujLYvBJfHg","target":"reci5XsSfPw9RZWBA","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1FAvujLYvBJfHg","target":"recOEXTM57COt0tET","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1FAvujLYvBJfHg","target":"recLFwe2uKBqJwmWn","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1FAvujLYvBJfHg","target":"recwqzXQjpmdyyW9y","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1FAvujLYvBJfHg","target":"recdIZxgxO61iLEXm","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1FAvujLYvBJfHg","target":"recBOUtTncbBlfEn9","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1FAvujLYvBJfHg","target":"recjNRR60PAuFtjha","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1FAvujLYvBJfHg","target":"recL1WV82pXaRBQ59","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1FAvujLYvBJfHg","target":"rectrAkGtrZH5LMp8","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1FAvujLYvBJfHg","target":"recwFUncFiNWPsPWN","label":"mentions"},{"source":"rec1FAvujLYvBJfHg","target":"recYsXWjhw6FUqHLY","label":"mentions"}],"verses":[{"id":"recGRpoot23nOgTS3","ref":"1Chr.21.1","text":"And Satan stood up against Israel, and provoked David to number Israel.","year":-1017},{"id":"recvyCnLOdVCoTEDQ","ref":"1Chr.21.2","text":"And David said to Joab and to the rulers of the people, Go, number Israel from Beersheba even to Dan; and bring the number of them to me, that I may know it.","year":-1017},{"id":"recuvecooSkRI0LCG","ref":"1Chr.21.3","text":"And Joab answered, The LORD make his people an hundred times so many more as they be: but, my lord the king, are they not all my lord’s servants? why then doth my lord require this thing? why will he be a cause of trespass to Israel?","year":-1017},{"id":"recqAAatUCN8JDY99","ref":"1Chr.21.4","text":"Nevertheless the king’s word prevailed against Joab. Wherefore Joab departed, and went throughout all Israel, and came to Jerusalem.","year":-1017},{"id":"recKoBhgneEPbrit3","ref":"1Chr.21.5","text":"And Joab gave the sum of the number of the people unto David. And all they of Israel were a thousand thousand and an hundred thousand men that drew sword: and Judah was four hundred threescore and ten thousand men that drew sword.","year":-1017},{"id":"recVj0CujZDBtRxZi","ref":"1Chr.21.6","text":"But Levi and Benjamin counted he not among them: for the king’s word was abominable to Joab.","year":-1017},{"id":"rechFuwPwV5A5u5dV","ref":"1Chr.21.7","text":"And God was displeased with this thing; therefore he smote Israel.","year":-1017},{"id":"recFuOmftJYRN2VqC","ref":"1Chr.21.8","text":"And David said unto God, I have sinned greatly, because I have done this thing: but now, I beseech thee, do away the iniquity of thy servant; for I have done very foolishly.","year":-1017}]}
